text: Gem County is a county in the U.S. state of Idaho. As of the 2020 census, 19,123 people lived there. The county seat and largest city is Emmett. == Communities == === City === * Emmett === Unincorporated communities === * Letha * Ola * Sweet == References == Category:1915 establishments in Idaho Category:Idaho counties
